      "content": "# never import error classes manually in reducer code\n\n```typescript\n// ❌ Don't manually import error classes\nimport { MissingIdError } from \"../../gen/module-name/error.js\";\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"message\");\n\n// ❌ Don't use nested access patterns\nthrow new errors.ModuleName.MissingIdError(\"message\");\n\n// ✅ Just reference the error by name — auto-imported\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"message\");\n```\n\nSince [[error classes in reducers are auto-imported by name reference]], the code generator scans for error class names and inserts the correct imports. Manual imports conflict with auto-generated ones, creating duplicate import errors or path mismatches.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
